Council reduced the proposed 5.5% tax increase to a final 4.6%, lower than the rate of inflation ‚Äì 7.7%. This mean in real dollars taxes have gone down from last year. On the average home, the increase means $7/ month, or $84/year.

A key in these economically challenging times was to make every dollar count. We are committed to holding the line on spending, fiscal responsibility, and delivering excellence in municipal services to our citizens.
On November 24, 2022, #Strathco council passed a unanimous budget for 2023. We acted in response to overriding external factors: inflation, supply chain issues, and rising interest rates.
